Over the course of 14 months, from August 2011 to October 2012, the Northeast United States was hit by three major disasters: Hurricane Irene, Tropical Storm Lee, and Superstorm Sandy. In the State of New York, this resulted in damage to over 300,000 homes, many of them destroyed by flood waters and wind. HORNE Government Services currently provides guidance for individuals and families still recovering almost 5 years later.

Have you ever met someone who gives you freedom?

Freedom to be yourself in your entirety

Freedom to escape previous restrictions and convictions 
Freedom to stop listening to the distorted noise surrounding

Freedom to explore your own mind

Freedom to truly love yourself as a working progress

Freedom to understand why you are who you are

What circumstances and lessons bought you to this moment in time

And which need to be forgiven and let go of

Freedom to not feel judgement or critique

You don’t need anyone to give you your freedom

Your freedom is within you

Once you find your key and unlock your prison cell

You will see that the enforcer is invisible 
But sometimes we need a little direction when looking for the key

A little logical advice and wisdom

A little assistance when trying to locate our treasures

A little fire to ignite our own

Have you ever met someone who gives you freedom?
Repost: @mslissashanee
